      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Introduction</h3>Let us begin by exploring some of the musical instruments found in Caral, Peru, as shown in <b>Figure 1</b>:</p><p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"img0\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img0', '0%')\" src=\"images/Caral/MusicCaral.jpg\" class=\"imgcenter\"/><b>Figure 1</b>: Section of painel found in archaeological site of Caral, courtesy of © ZonaArqueólogicaCaral (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('720f6dfd-4b86-4e07-a887-1010e1041a4d'); return false;\">Ruta Caral, <htdate0></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('03c3743c-d268-4730-ba8e-d36b5c49e781'); return false;\">Youtube - Caral Perú Oficial, <htdate1></a>). Photo taken on <htdate2>, during a visit to the site.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2024",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2024",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2017",
                     "month": "6",
                     "day": "13"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "In this image, we have 32 flutes aligned vertically side by side.",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\">?</div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: Couting with our body</b><br />There are more musical instruments in <b>Figure 1</b>  than we have fingers on our hands. How can we count these instruments?</div></div></center></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_together",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Together we are capable</h3>When we cannot count alone, we can ask for help. In this way, we are able to count:</p><p><table class=\"tawapukllay\"><tr><th colspan=\"2\">First person</th><th colspan=\"2\">Second person</th><th colspan=\"2\">Third person</th><th>Fourth person</th></tr>  <tr><td><img id=\"img5900\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img5900', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/5Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td><img id=\"img5901\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img5901', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/5Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td><img id=\"img5902\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img5902', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/5Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td><img id=\"img5903\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img5903', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/5Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td><img id=\"img5904\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img5904', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/5Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td><img id=\"img5905\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img5905', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/5Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td><img id=\"img5906\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img5906', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/2Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td></tr></table></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p>Counting with the help of others solves our problem once again. But take a look at <b>Figure 2</b>, taken in Copán, Honduras, which contains the largest known text from the Maya region:</p><p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"img8\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img8', '0%')\" src=\"images/Copan/CopanWholeTextStelaAltar.png\" class=\"imgcenter\"/><b>Figure 2</b>: Altar, stele, and the largest hieroglyphic text at the Copan site (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('1e007481-9bd3-4a09-ad4d-6e812fe79641'); return false;\">Instituto Hondureño de Antropologia e Historia, <htdate0></a>). Photo taken on <htdate1>, during a visit to the site.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2024",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2017",
                     "month": "6",
                     "day": "13"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "An altar, a stela, and the largest hieroglyphic inscription at the site, constructed in a ladder-like format.",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p>This hieroglyphic text, present in the background of the image, requires multiple people to count everything. Let us think of another solution:</p><p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\">?</div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 2: Thinking together</b><br />Looking at your fingers, can you find another way to count?</div></div></center></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_ancient",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Another solution</h3>The necessity to count did not appear recently. It has existed for a long time, dating back to when there were no cities or houses built. We know this thanks to scientists who discovered bones with marks in different places (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('a4f22e25-5839-407f-a1aa-634521d52b42'); return false;\">González Redondo, Francisco A., et al., <htdate0>, pp. 174 - 177, 180 - 182</a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('ceffba8a-43be-4de3-a5c8-27cdf81311b1'); return false;\">Puente, Francisco Barriga, <htdate1>, pp. 21 - 23</a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('cd61bc64-1358-4bfd-b343-3629facaa3b4'); return false;\">González Redondo, Francisco A., <htdate2></a>):</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2010",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2020",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2024",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"img9\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img9', '0%')\" src=\"images/ResearchGate/Figura-9-Hueso-de-Lebombo.png\" class=\"imgcenter\"/><b>Figure 1</b>: Representation of baboon bone adorned with markings. This image, credited to Enrique Silván Pobes, is featured in the scholarly work of Francisco A. Gonzáles Redondo et al.<br />The original is available in ResearchNet (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('adaed4fb-9c50-4ef9-ab79-c65f3c0629b8'); return false;\">González Redondo, Francisco A., et al., <htdate0></a>), and its inclusion here is made possible by the authorization of Doctor Francisco A. Gonzales Redondo.</p><p>Over the centuries, various numeration systems have been utilized, some of which endure to this day. In the following sections, we present an overview of contemporary systems alongside those that have recently fallen out of use.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2010",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p>Observe that the marks on the bones resemble our fingers.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_conclusion",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Conclusion</h3>In this text, we learned that with the help of others, we can count even more, but we also observed that this does not solve all issues.</p><p>We also learned that after using our fingers to count, the next step was to make marks. This was not the only solution found. In the next texts, we will explore more options created for counting.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      }
